---
// src/pages/about.astro
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import NavBlock from "../components/NavBlock.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Quirgs"
  description="What Quirgs is, the governance-first thesis behind it, who builds it, and how the platform is operated and maintained."
  terminalPath="~/about"
>
  <NavBlock currentPath="/about/" />

  <div class="line">
    <span class="prompt">admin@quirgs</span><span class="path">~/about</span
    ><span class="text-bright">$</span>&nbsp;cat about.md
  </div>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <div class="detail-header">
    <h1 class="text-bright">About Quirgs</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Governance first. Build accordingly.</p>
  </div>

  <p>
    Quirgs is a governance-first AI product platform. It exists to make
    responsible AI development practical — turning standards like the EU AI Act,
    the NIST AI Risk Management Framework, and ISO/IEC 42001 into tooling a
    builder can actually run, rather than documents a team reads once and
    shelves.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">The Thesis</h2>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    Most AI governance arrives too late — bolted on after a system ships, when
    changing it is expensive. Quirgs takes the opposite position: governance is
    a build-time concern. Inventory what your AI systems do, place human
    checkpoints where AI output drives decisions, and align to recognized
    standards from the start. The platform packages those three pillars —
    Inventory, Checkpoints, and Standards Alignment — into installable tools.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">What Quirgs Distributes</h2>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    The platform delivers governance work in three formats: <span
      class="text-bright">Skills</span
    > (installable agent tools that produce structured compliance analysis and draft
    documents), <span class="text-bright">Guides</span> (reference material for builders),
    and <span class="text-bright">Tools</span>
    (governance utilities like the human-in-the-loop approval gate). The skills registry
    is free, open-source, and inspectable before install.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">Who Builds It</h2>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    Quirgs is built and operated by Torrey Adams (<a
      href="https://torreyladams.com"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener">unqdlphn</a
    >), an independent builder focused on AI governance and responsible product
    development. The platform is run as an independent project — small,
    transparent about its scope, and deliberate about what it claims. Quirgs
    also publishes educational content on building AI products responsibly via
    its <a href="https://youtube.com/@quirgs" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
      >YouTube channel</a
    > and <a href="https://x.com/QuirgsAI" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
      >@QuirgsAI</a
    >.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">How It's Operated</h2>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    The platform governs its own AI use through the same framework it teaches.
    AI assistance used in content and development is disclosed in full on
    the&nbsp;
    <a href="/transparency/">transparency notice</a>, every change ships through
    human-reviewed checkpoints, and the security posture is documented openly on
    the <a href="/security/">security page</a>. Source is on&nbsp;
    <a href="https://github.com/unqdlphn/quirgs" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
      >GitHub</a
    >.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">Honest Scope</h2>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    Quirgs accelerates governance work; it does not replace professional
    judgment. The skills are governance support tools, not legal advice, and not
    a substitute for qualified counsel or a certified auditor. They are built to
    get a team from a blank page to a reviewable draft faster — the review still
    belongs to you.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <div>
    Get started &rarr; <a href="/skills/">/skills/</a> &middot; Questions? See&nbsp;
    <a href="/support/">/support/</a>.
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
